This song, as the title suggests, is about freedom. In the changing world the common people are losing their freedom to the governments and big corporations, this song is a fight against the system.

The track contains samples from the song “This Feeling (Freedom) by Julius Brockington and the Magic Force to the extent that he has a writing credit. It was also released as a single on December 2nd, 2003 with the track “One of Them” as its B-side.

songs.title: Work it Out

description.plain:
In the summer of 2005 Jurassic 5 opened for Dave Matthews Band on 4 of their tour stops. This time together was no doubt the genesis for this collabo.

Not that anyone cares, but I was at the [June 4th , 2005 show] (http://antsmarching.org/tour/ViewShow.php?ShowID=3488), and Dave himself came out and introduced J5 before their set. He mentioned that he loved them and wanted to work with them in the future. So here you have it. (Cut Chemist was not at this show and was not on the Feedback album. They did play the song “Red Hot” at this show, that would also be their first single on the Feedback album).

This was also the last single that Jurassic 5 ever released before disbanding.
